Warning for deep depression to the East of Sri Lanka. Issued by the Natural Hazards Early Warning Centre, Department of Meteorology. Issued at 07.30 p.m. on 09 January 2026 for the period until 07.30 p.m. on 10 January 2026

For the land and the sea areas around the island TAKE ACTION! The deep depression over the southwest Bay of Bengal was located about 110 km northeast of Batticaloa at 7:00 p.m. on 9 January 2026. It is very likely to move northwestwards and cross the Sri Lanka coast between Trincomalee and Jaffna tomorrow afternoon (10 January 2026).
